    {"repo": "github.com/gcc-mirror/gcc", "path": "gcc/final.cc", "symbol": "pass_final::execute"}
  ],
  "text": "GCC's RTL (Register Transfer Language) intermediate representation pass chain is structured through a class hierarchy defined in gcc/tree-pass.h. The base opt_pass class (lines 73-113) provides the framework for all optimization passes. Derived from this is rtl_opt_pass (lines 125-133), which serves as the base class for all RTL-level optimization passes.\n\nThe RTL pass chain begins with pass_expand in gcc/cfgexpand.cc (lines 6994-7020). This is a critical transition pass that converts GIMPLE intermediate representation to RTL using the rtl_opt_pass framework. The pass_expand class (line 7010) inherits from rtl_opt_pass and implements execute() method that performs the gimple-to-RTL transformation.\n\nFollowing pass_expand, multiple RTL optimization passes are executed. A representative example is pass_cse (Common Subexpression Elimination) in gcc/cse.cc (lines 7628-7655). This rtl_opt_pass-derived class performs CSE optimization at the RTL level. Its execute() method calls rest_of_handle_cse(), with a gate() check to ensure optimization is enabled.\n\nThe RTL pass chain concludes with pass_final in gcc/final.cc (lines 4327-4362). This pass is responsible for final code generation, converting the optimized RTL into assembly code. The pass_final class (line 4340) also inherits from rtl_opt_pass and implements execute() to call rest_of_handle_final().\n\nThe complete pass ordering is defined in gcc/passes.def (lines 460-572). The RTL passes are organized within pass_rest_of_compilation (lines 463-575), starting with pass_expand (line 460), followed by numerous RTL optimization passes like pass_cse (line 469), pass_jump (line 466), and many loop optimization passes, ultimately concluding with pass_final (line 572) in the pass_late_compilation section (lines 559-573).\n\nThis architecture demonstrates a clear separation of concerns: opt_pass provides the pass framework, rtl_opt_pass specializes it for RTL-level operations, and individual passes like pass_expand, pass_cse, and pass_final implement specific transformations. The pass pipeline is data-driven through gcc/passes.def, allowing flexible composition of optimization passes while maintaining consistent interfaces for pass registration and execution."
}

